  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: \r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.10.17-unstable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.17.8\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nCommit hash : 51de2bc\r\n\r\nBeacon Client: Lighthouse\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI ran a debug_setHead command, expecting Geth to go back to an earlier block, then reprocess blocks up to the current head.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nAfter running debug_setHead, Geth logged messages along the lines of \r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [03-22|12:50:24.055] Forkchoice requested sync to new head    number=102,027 hash=5acaf0..e063e1\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut never gave messages like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nChain head was updated \r\nImported new potential chain segment \r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nSync the Kiln tetstnet to current. Run debug_setHead to an earlier block.\r\n\r\n#### Other Notes\r\n\r\nFor Kiln this isn't a big deal - I was resynced in a matter of minutes - but on Mainnet recovering could potentially take days, so a change in this behavior could cause someone real problems.",
